02:18:14.240 --> 02:18:23.040
who trashed it, other than that, and I didn't want that. So I would ask a question, and I would see

02:18:23.120 --> 02:18:28.800
in the faces of my teachers, both those I didn't much care for, and those who were good teachers

02:18:28.800 --> 02:18:34.880
that I liked, fear. It was just fear. They didn't want to go there. They didn't want to answer my

02:18:34.880 --> 02:18:40.880
question. And after a while, I got to know some of them, and I found out why, because you don't

02:18:40.880 --> 02:18:45.360
know how the rest of the class is going to understand this. Either they would have to say,

02:18:45.360 --> 02:18:50.160
I don't know, which would be the honest truth for many of them, but a professor does not want to

02:18:50.160 --> 02:18:57.520
say in a classroom, I don't know, that it's not cool. Or if they knew, they'd have to say something

02:18:58.240 --> 02:19:02.400
that indicated they didn't know really much, and they weren't even going to do that.

02:19:02.400 --> 02:19:09.920
Or they would know something, and maybe that would be because they were interested. They did not want

02:19:09.920 --> 02:19:17.280
the rest of the students to begin to say, oh, you know, Professor Smith, he's interested.

02:19:17.600 --> 02:19:22.000
Mm-mm. This is not good for your career. You don't know how this is going to

02:19:22.000 --> 02:19:27.760
play out. Who's going to say what to whom? And I could see in their faces what I later learned,

02:19:27.760 --> 02:19:33.440
because they told me, don't come to my office hours. We're in the office. We can talk about it.

02:19:33.440 --> 02:19:35.680
But that's how bad it was.

02:19:36.400 --> 02:19:38.240
Is it not still?

02:19:38.240 --> 02:19:44.720
